cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about generative modeling of text using variational autoencoders (VAE) with a new type of decoder, a dilated CNN. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the trade-off between contextual capacity and encoding information, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of CNNs and the investigation of semi-supervised and unsupervised labeling tasks suggest that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
